# Force textual diffs for our source/text extensions regardless of content.
#
# Without this, a stray control byte (e.g. an accidentally-embedded raw NUL — this has
# happened repeatedly to agent-generated Kotlin edits in this repo) makes git's content-based
# binary heuristic misclassify the whole file as binary. `git diff`/`git show` then print
# "Binary files ... differ" instead of a reviewable line-by-line diff, so the defect can slip
# through `git diff`-based review invisibly. The `diff` attribute (not `text` — that also
# triggers EOL renormalization, which we don't want) is display-only: it forces the internal
# diff machinery to treat matching paths as text, making any embedded binary byte immediately
# visible as a real diff hunk instead of vanishing into "Bin".
*.kt diff
*.kts diff
*.md diff
*.js diff
*.json diff
*.sql diff
